<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD CUP SECURITY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * The World Cup will bring the eyes of the world upon Los Angeles this summer, 
with an estimated television viewing audience of over 2 billion people for the 
final game. Police Commissioner Enrique Hernandez complains ("Reimbursement for 
World Cup Security Urged," May 4) that the city will have to foot the security 
bill for the estimated 280,000 visitors who will be attending the World Cup. In 
light of the fact that these visitors will be spending millions of dollars in 
our city and that the city will get an unmeasurable amount of free tourism 
advertising, Hernandez's request is shortsighted and petty. 
</P>
<P>
 ANDREW WOLFBERG 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Monica 
</P>
</TEXT>
