<HEADLINE>
<P>
PRISONERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * After reading "Prison Bars Can't Keep Out Mother's Love" (May 8), I was 
almost physically ill.Are we supposed to feel sorry for these women whose sons 
are in prison for committing horrible, inhuman crimes? Sorry, but they get no 
sympathy from me. 
</P>
<P>
 My 21-year-old son was murdered in 1989. How do you think I feel on Mother's 
Day? And having that story on the front page sure didn't make me feel any 
better. 
</P>
<P>
 ANN ERICKSON 
</P>
<P>
 Lake Forest 
</P>
