 It's time to look at the mind-bogglingly generous amounts of money city 
councils and juries award these days and keep in mind who really pays these 
bills! No amount of money can make up for what any victim suffers, but if the 
perpetrator isn't paying the damages, then the notion of punishment harks back 
to the days of whipping boys -- the angry get to feel good, the guilty are 
warned, and the real punishment is passed along to the innocent. 
</P>
