<P>
APPLICATIONS OPEN FOR SPEED HUMPS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Los Angeles residents can begin applying to have speed humps installed on 
residential streets after City Council approval of the program this week. 
</P>
<P>
 To get the speed-reduction devices installed, residents must collect 
signatures from 75% of the neighbors on their block. In most neighborhoods, 
they also will have to raise about $6,000 to pay for the standard set of three 
humps. 
</P>
<P>
 Applications can be submitted through City Council offices or through the 
city's Department of Transportation. 
