<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: ANAHEIM; LUPUS SUPPORT GROUP WILL MEET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An attorney will discuss how those with lupus can receive Social Security 
benefits at the Wednesday meeting of the Orange County Lupus Support Group. 
</P>
<P>
 The speech by Santa Ana attorney Judith L. Rosenbloom will take place at 7 
p.m. at Anaheim Memorial Hospital's Classrooms C and D. The hospital is at 1211 
W. La Palma Ave. 
</P>
<P>
 Lupus is an autoimmune disease. It affects people of all ages but is most 
commonly diagnosed in women during their child-bearing years. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (714) 668-1623. 
</P>
</TEXT>
