<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE TENNIS; ORANGE COAST WINS WOMEN'S TEAM TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Kamala Raj Kumar won a 3 1/2-hour match to help Orange Coast win the State 
women's dual team tennis title with a 6-2 victory over Chabot Thursday at La 
Costa Resort in Carlsbad. 
</P>
<P>
 Raj Kumar, playing at No. 4 singles, won, 1-6, 6-3, 7-6.She was trailing, 1-5, 
in the third set, but won four consecutive games to tie it, 5-5. In the 
third-set tie-breaker, Raj Kumar was down, 2-5, but rallied to win, 10-8. 
</P>
<P>
 Toowee Cao of OCC beat Amy Peterson, the sixth-ranked player in the state, 
6-1, 6-3, at No. 2 singles. 
</P>
<P>
 Amy Cook won, 6-4, 6-3, and Heather Rainey won, 7-6, 6-1, in singles for the 
Pirates. Cao and Raj Kumar teamed to win in doubles, 6-2, 6-2. Cook and Rainey 
closed out the match with a 6-3, 6-1 victory in doubles. 
</P>
<P>
 It was the first State title for OCC and Coach Janice Maran since 1990. The 
Pirates, who won the Orange Empire Conference last month, ended the season, 
19-0. The Pirates beat College of the Desert, 5-1, in the Southern California 
final Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Chabot finished 18-1. 
</P>
</TEXT>
