<HEADLINE>
<P>
O'CONNELL CUTS FOOT BUT STILL WINS SURF HEAT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE REILLEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Laguna Niguel's Pat O'Connell won his main event first-round heat at the Bud 
Pro Surfing tour Thursday at Huntington State Beach. And he picked up a few 
stitches in the process. 
</P>
<P>
 O'Connell, the star of the new surf movie "Endless Summer II," fell on a wave 
late in the heat and suffered a deep cut on his foot from a skeg on the bottom 
of his board. Lifeguards treated the wound, then took O'Connell to the hospital 
for stitches. 
</P>
<P>
 O'Connell's lead held through the end of the heat and he advanced to today's 
second round along with Huntington Beach's Kirk Tice, who finished second in 
the heat. O'Connell is expected to compete despite the injury. 
</P>
<P>
 Competition resumes at 7 a.m. today with the final eight first-round heats, 
followed by the second round. Expected to compete are former world-champion 
Kelly Slater, defending world champion Derek Ho, Newport Beach's Richie 
Collins, and San Clemente's Dino Andino, Shane Beschen and Mike Parsons. MIKE 
REILLEY 
</P>
