COMMUNITY COLLEGE BASEBALL; GONZALES NAMED MOST VALUABLE IN CONFERENCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Andy Gonzales, a second baseman and relief pitcher from Cypress, was selected 
as the most valuable player of the Orange Empire Conference by a vote of 
coaches. 
</P>
<P>
 Gonzales, a sophomore from Tustin High, hit .347 with five home runs and drove 
in 24 runs in 24 conference games for Cypress, which won the conference title 
by a game over Riverside.Gonzales also was 2-2 with four saves. He had 21 
strikeouts and gave up eight hits in 15 innings. Cypress' Scott Pickler was 
coach of the year. 
</P>
<P>
 Riverside's Jeff Barker went 8-2 with a 1.75 earned-run average and was 
selected pitcher of the year. FIRST TEAM 
