<P>
 The skies over Moorpark College will be flecked with hundreds of multicolored 
kites Saturday when the college hosts a May Kite Festival. 
</P>
<P>
 Organizers came up with the idea this year as a way to "get the community 
involved in a big way" at the college, said event coordinator Susan Jeffers. 
</P>
<P>
 "The object is to get people out here to have fun," she said. 
</P>
<P>
 Included on the day's agenda is a kite-flying demonstration inside the school 
gym by a nationally recognized kite flyer. 
</P>
<P>
 "These new kites are totally amazing," Jeffers said. "They don't need any 
wind. They lift off with just the motion of walking." 
</P>
<P>
 Along with the demonstration, kite "dogfights" and kite "ballets," the event 
will include several contests in which awards for the most creative and most 
aerodynamically designed kites will be awarded. 
</P>
<P>
 The festival runs from 10 a.m. to 3 p.m. It will be held on the lower athletic 
field south of the college gymnasium. Admission is $3, with children under 12 
admitted free. Parking is also free. 
