<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY: THOUSAND OAKS; SYMPHONY BENEFIT CONCERT CANCELED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEPHANIE SIMON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Conejo Symphony pops concert scheduled for Sunday at Cal Lutheran University 
has been canceled. 
</P>
<P>
 Designed as a benefit for the Conejo Symphony Orchestra, the afternoon event 
would have included a concert, arts show and street fair.But symphony 
organizers realized this week that they could not get the program organized in 
time. 
</P>
<P>
 "It just became logistically too difficult," Conejo Symphony Director Everett 
Ascher said. The group began planning the event at the end of March but found 
that "45 days was just not enough time to do this," he added. 
</P>
<P>
 Ascher had hoped to raise $5,000 with the street fair and pops concert. But 
even with the cancellation, he predicted the symphony would reach its goal of 
raising $25,000 this year. 
</P>
<P>
 To help reach that target, symphony members are organizing a June 5 benefit 
called "A Day at Ascot." Scheduled for 11:30 a.m. at the Foxfield Riding 
Academy in Westlake Village, the event will feature a champagne brunch and an 
equestrian drill team performance. Tickets cost $55. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information about the June benefit, call the symphony office at 
495-6833. STEPHANIE SIMON 
</P>
</TEXT>
