<P>
WORLD IN BRIEF; JAPAN; EMPRESS REGAINS ABILITY TO SPEAK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Japan's Empress Michiko has almost fully recovered the power of speech, nearly 
seven months after being struck with a mystery ailment, the imperial palace 
said.The empress collapsed on her 59th birthday Oct. 20. Although first signs 
pointed to a minor stroke, palace officials said later tests showed no brain 
damage. They attributed her inability to speak to deep depression over critical 
articles in the press. 
</P>
