ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: HUNTINGTON BEACH; SCHOOL FOR AT-RISK YOUTH WINS AWARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Valley Vista Continuation High School, which serves public school students 
with problems and special needs in Huntington Beach, Westminster and Fountain 
Valley, has won statewide recognition as a model school. 
</P>
<P>
 The designation came from the state Department of Education and was announced 
Tuesday night during the board meeting of the Huntington Beach Union High 
School District.Valley Vista Continuation High is in Fountain Valley.  
</P>
<P>
 "Valley Vista was one of a select group recognized by the state for its 
exemplary service to at-risk youth," the school board said in a statement. "We 
extend our congratulations to Dick Maynard, principal of Valley Vista 
Continuation High School, and the instructional and support staff who have made 
possible this unique recognition." 
</P>
<P>
 Maynard said Valley Vista was among 17 continuation high schools selected by 
the state this year as model institutions. He said Valley Vista is the only 
such school in Orange County picked for the designation. 
