<HEADLINE>
<P>
SANTA CLARITA / ANTELOPE VALLEY; NEW SCHEDULE CLOSES CITY HALL TODAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DOUGLAS ALGER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Residents who try to go to City Hall today will be out of luck -- and not 
because it's Friday the 13th. 
</P>
<P>
 Instead, this is the first closure of city offices under Santa Clarita's new 
operating schedule, modified so employees can work 80 hours over nine days and 
not 10.One of the reasons: The city has about 185 employees and must adhere to 
South Coast Air Quality Management District standards that call for agencies 
with 100 or more workers to reduce car trips. 
</P>
<P>
 City employees previously worked a modified schedule with half of them off 
Mondays. Department heads said that after two years half-staffing days had not 
proved productive and asked to shift the schedules so all workers had the same 
day off. 
</P>
<P>
 Non-administrative tasks, such as maintenance work or emergency services, will 
still be conducted every day of the week as necessary. 
</P>
<P>
 City offices are open 7:30 a.m. to 5:30 p.m. Mondays through Thursdays and 8 
a.m. to 5 p.m. on alternating Fridays. DOUGLAS ALGER 
</P>
</TEXT>
