LICENSE PLATE HOLDER SALES TO BENEFIT ARTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Artist Wayne Thiebaud has collaborated with San Diego's Visual Asylum to 
design a license plate holder that reads "State of the Arts" in bold white 
letters on a deep blue background. 
</P>
<P>
 The holder was commissioned by the California Confederation for the Arts and 
proceeds will support campaigns for increased arts education and funding for 
the arts. 
</P>
<P>
 The holder sells for $12 and can be used with regular license plates or with 
California Arts Council arts plates also designed by Thiebaud and available 
from the Department of Motor Vehicles. 
</P>
<P>
