<P>
BRIEFCASE: SMALL AND MINORITY BUSINESSES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Susan Christian / Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 AST Co-Founder to Talk: Thomas Yuen, co-founder and former co-chairman of 
Irvine computer maker AST Research, will speak Tuesday at the Orange Coast 
Venture Group's monthly luncheon. 
</P>
<P>
 Yuen, who is chairman of a number of start-up companies in Orange County, will 
talk about key reasons for AST's success and how lessons learned there can be 
applied to other new companies. 
</P>
<P>
 The Orange Coast Venture Group is a nonprofit networking organization for 
business leaders, entrepreneurs and venture capitalists. 
</P>
<P>
 The Tuesday luncheon seminar will start at 11:30 a.m. at the Center Club in 
Costa Mesa. Cost for non-members is $35. The $250 annual membership fee covers 
the luncheon for members. For more information, call 859-3646. 
